  "title": "Amazon Q2 2024 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2024-08-01T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2024_Q2",
  "location": "Seattle, WA",
  "url": "https://ir.aboutamazon.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "andy-jassy",
      "speaker_name": "Andy Jassy",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q2 was a very strong quarter. AWS revenue grew 19% year-over-year to $26.3 billion. We are seeing a substantial uptick in demand from enterprise customers moving workloads to AWS to take advantage of our AI services. We expect AWS revenue growth to accelerate in the second half of 2024 as we clear through our capacity constraints, which we are actively resolving. We believe AWS will reach $120 billion in annualized revenue run rate before the end of 2024."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "brian-olsavsky",
      "speaker_name": "Brian Olsavsky",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:20:00",
      "text": "Total net sales were $148 billion, up 10% year-over-year. Operating income was $14.7 billion, representing a 9.9% operating margin — a record for the company. Advertising revenue grew 19% to $14.7 billion. We continue to invest heavily in fulfillment and AI infrastructure. For Q3, we expect net sales of $154 to $158.5 billion and operating income of $11.5 to $15 billion."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Andy, can you speak to how you're thinking about the long-term AWS margin profile as AI workloads become a larger part of the mix?"
    }
  ],
